<BaseLayout title="Company | BeaconGuard Assurance">
  <section>
    <h1>Company</h1>
  <p>BeaconGuard Assurance builds enterprise governance infrastructure for AI runtime operations and financial workflow control boundaries.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Mission</h2>
    <p>
      Our mission is to make AI authorization dependable, reviewable, and operationally practical with bounded trust.
      BeaconGuard reduces ambiguity by separating deterministic policy control, enforcement, and evidence generation
      into a clear fail-closed runtime boundary.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>What We Are</h2>
    <p>
      BeaconGuard is an infrastructure product for enterprise teams building AI into
      mission-critical financial workflows.
    </p>
    <p>
      We focus on deterministic policy control, fail-closed behavior, and evidence-ready operations.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Why We Built This</h2>
    <p>
      Enterprise teams need governance that scales with systems, not with exception handling.
      We built BeaconGuard for teams that want clear financial control boundaries, replayable outcomes,
      and practical proof for governance and assurance conversations.
    </p>
  </section>

